    "description": "Grow your career with Bank of India! We are hiring a Risk Analyst for our Chandigarh team. Be part of a workplace that celebrates innovation, diversity, and performance.\n\nAbout Bank of India:\nBank of India is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Develop financial models and projections for business planning\n• Prepare MIS reports for senior management review\n• Coordinate with external auditors during annual audits\n• Ensure compliance with tax regulations and statutory requirements\n• Manage accounts payable and accounts receivable functions\n• Process payroll and manage employee reimbursements\n• Monitor financial performance against targets and provide variance analysis\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Bachelor's degree in a relevant field\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Financial Modeling\n• Proficiency in Credit Analysis\n• Proficiency in VBA\n• Proficiency in GST\n• Proficiency in SAP FICO\n• Proficiency in MS Excel\n• Proficiency in Risk Management\n• Proficiency in Ind AS\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Chandigarh, Punjab, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Bank of India!",
